sql:
SELECT MAX(version_number) AS latest_version
FROM data_versions
WHERE experiment_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
; Comprehensive profile implies a detailed overview; 
; Total accesses, view accesses, edit accesses, and delete accesses refer to the number of times users interacted with the experiment in these manners;
; Unique access dates indicate the number of different days on which the experiment was accessed;
; Total feedbacks, suggestions, and issues pertain to user feedback categorized into these types.

; The logarithmic volume and quality measurements refer to the values in the 'log_volume1' and 'log_quality' columns in the 'data_records' table; 
; Passing quality checks is based on the 'status' column in the 'data_quality_assurance' table having a value of 'pass';
; Having at least one QA entry means the experiment_id exists in the 'data_quality_assurance' table.

